The paper deals with the problem of decentralized estimation of a stochastic process by multiple agents, which is a topic in multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and control theory (cs.SY). The use of a communication graph suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a novel approach to decentralized estimation that involves a combination of common and local estimates, which may be of interest to researchers in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
